body:
Story time!

Yesterday when my history professor said “my last class will be December 13th,” I turned to my friend and said “is that next week?” She shook her head yes as my eyes went wide. She asked if I was okay, and I said yes, but in reality I was actually going “oh my god that’s Taylor’s birthday. It stuck up so soon. It’s next week. She’s turning 29. She said she would released another album before turning 30. IT’S HER BIRTHDAY?! NEXT WEEK?!AHHHHHHHH”

title: why she's important.
body: hey, so I thought id share my story on taylor and why she means so much to me and why she is so close to my heart. taylor has gotten me through almost absolutely everything. she has grown up with me. she has been there for my happiness, depression, breakups, anger, confusion, my hopes, my dreams, my fantasies, my family, drama,, confusion, and so on. for every emotion she has song for me. for every moment in my life she was there. I had fallen in love with Taylor at the age of four and have loved her ever sense the “fearless” album was released. she’s always been with me. I cannot remember a time she wasn’t. i remember how I had started at a new school in the fourth grade and had no friends and everyone thought I was weird. 1989 got me through the hard times and had helped me get through it and not care what anyone thought and how I just needed to shake it off. she taught me to be strong, she taught me how to love, she helped me find who I was. she is the reason I am who I am today and is the reason I have gotten through what I have today. she isn’t just a singer I love. she is a part of me. and for that I will always love her dearley. thank you for reading if you’re here. and to Taylor, thanks for being here when no one else was. you truly are my absolute world.

blog.name: tswiftandtsn
blog.title: taylor done played us all
blog.description: I'm Kayla. 21. And I make no apologies for who I am.

summary: hi there Kayla!! it’s your secret santa. I completely understand what you mean by looking forward to not having stuff to do! I...
question: hi there Kayla!! it’s your secret santa. I completely understand what you mean by looking forward to not having stuff to do! I have to study for my exams during the holidays but it’ll still be nice not having to go to lectures and seminars. I’m sending you good vibes and luck for your papers and finals 💓 now I was wondering, what’s your favourite ts album? top 5 songs? and what other artists do you like? I hope you have a lovely tuesday - ss ✨
answer:
Thank you so much and same to you. You’re an amazing secret santa by the way and I can’t wait to know you. And you’re good I get it, I mean it’s 2am here and I’m up because I’m an insomniac who doubles as a masochist apparently since I have to get up at 7. 

I’ve gone back and forth so many times about my favorite TS album. For a long time I thought Red. But then I sort of calculated based on my ranking of the songs and how the numbers averaged out and by that it pointed to Speak Now being my favorite. But also I love Reputation, so much. It might be because I feel like it’s the album that most speaks to me personally or maybe just cause it helped me through a rough time, but currently I’m leaning towards Reputation as my favorite album. 

Top 5 songs: I’m super basic so my favorite is All Too Well but I mean I suppose there’s a reason it’s everyone’s favorite it’s just so beautiful. 

Second is Call It What You Want and Third is You Are In Love, I think those are just very beautiful and it perfectly encapsulates what I guess I’ve always wanted out of someone I love, I never really got into the more fairy tale, super perfection sort of love that was described as prime in the earlier songs. But in Call It What You Want, the lines: ‘Trust him like a brother’ and ‘I want to wear his initial on a chain round my neck not because he owns me but because he really knows me’, just really stick with me cause I’ve always wanted to be with someone who is super close to me and knows me and gets me and someone I trust so deeply cause trust and loyalty have always been the key traits I desire in friendship and love, and it’s the same reason I love You Are In Love cause the line ‘You fight and you talk. One night he wakes, strange look on his face pauses, then says, you’re my best friend’ also has that same tie, I’ve always wanted to be with someone who was my best friend basically and someone I can fight and talk to still be okay with cause I’m someone who argues just to argue I suppose but it’s cause that’s my learning style and it’s how I learn I debate people and think aloud and force them to engage and build their argument against me cause I want them to give me everything they know or think and have all these and I think that’s the best way to get it, and a lot of people don’t understand that so I’ve always really loved that line and it’s made those songs for me.

Fourth is probably Dear John, that one is just really relatable to me and also has the deep emotional sort of narrative that makes All Too Well so great too.

Fifth, this one changes around a lot for me, but right now it’s Come Back Be Here. I really love that one cause I think we’ve all had someone who even if their not across the country or whatever feels far away and we miss them and want them back or maybe they’ve changed but just the idea of distance.

(Sorry for those long symposiums)

As for other artists, Bastille is probably my second favorite they get me pretty good like Taylor. Other’s include Queen, One Direction (my deep emotional cornerstone), Harry Styles & Niall Horan as solo artists, My Chemical Romance (They also get me pretty deep), Ed Sheeran (also gets me), Panic! At The Disco, Pink Floyd (Also gets me), Fleetwood Mac (Love them), Michael Jackson, Justin Timberlake, Adele, The 1975, Halsey, The Chainsmokers, 5 Seconds of Summer. I think those are the ones where I love at least 5+ songs from their discography.

body:
